name: Sanitize user inputs
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: User inputs used directly without sanitization
then: Sanitize all user inputs before processing or displaying
why: Prevents XSS attacks and data corruption.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use environment variables for sensitive data
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Hardcoded API keys, URLs, or sensitive configuration
then: Use environment variables with REACT_APP_ prefix
why: Prevents sensitive data from being exposed in client-side code.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Validate form inputs
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Form submissions without input validation
then: Implement proper form validation on both client and server side
why: Input validation prevents malicious data and improves user experience.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use HTTPS in production
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: HTTP URLs in production environment
then: Use HTTPS for all API calls and external resources
why: HTTPS encrypts data transmission and prevents man-in-the-middle attacks.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper CORS handling
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: API calls without proper CORS configuration
then: Ensure proper CORS setup and handle CORS errors gracefully
why: Proper CORS configuration prevents unauthorized cross-origin requests.
globs: ["frontend/src/services/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Sanitize HTML content
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: User content rendered as HTML without sanitization
then: Use DOMPurify or similar library to sanitize HTML content
why: Prevents XSS attacks through malicious HTML content.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Validate API responses
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: API responses used without validation
then: Validate API response structure and data types
why: Prevents runtime errors and potential security issues from malformed data.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use secure session management
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Sensitive data stored in localStorage or sessionStorage
then: Use secure session management and avoid storing sensitive data in browser storage
why: Browser storage is vulnerable to XSS attacks and should not contain sensitive data.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement rate limiting awareness
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: API calls without rate limiting consideration
then: Implement client-side rate limiting and handle rate limit errors gracefully
why: Rate limiting prevents abuse and improves API reliability.
globs: ["frontend/src/services/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/hooks/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Use secure headers
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: API requests without proper security headers
then: Include appropriate security headers in API requests
why: Security headers help prevent various types of attacks.
globs: ["frontend/src/services/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Validate file uploads
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: File uploads without validation
then: Validate file types, sizes, and content before upload
why: Prevents malicious file uploads and improves security.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use Content Security Policy
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: No Content Security Policy implementation
then: Implement CSP headers to prevent XSS and other injection attacks
why: CSP provides an additional layer of security against various attacks.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]
description:
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---
